## Step 19 — Production-Readiness and Markdown Cleanup

Before finalizing the chapter, do a production-readiness pass. Check for and resolve:

- leftover author comments, TODOs, or notes such as `<!-- ... -->` that are not intentional;
- placeholder text such as "elaborate here," "needs editing," or "turn this into…";
- raw local file paths such as `file:///G:/...`, `G:\...`, or bare quoted Windows image paths;
- broken or inconsistent image references;
- duplicated visuals (remove or move to an appendix);
- inconsistent heading capitalization;
- incomplete sections;
- old blockquote-style callouts (convert via Step 10);
- repeated explanations across multiple sections;
- missing captions, weak captions, or unclear alt text.

Do not leave visible editing notes in the final student-facing chapter unless explicitly instructed. If a note cannot be resolved confidently, surface it in the **Unresolved decisions** section of the Final Revision Report rather than leaving it inside the chapter body.

